place.name: TRYSULL
place.gazetteerText: TRYSULL, a parish, with a village, in Wolverhampton district, Stafford; 5½ miles SW of Wolverhampton r. station. It has a post-office under Wolverhampton; and it contains Seisdon hamlet and a workhouse. Acres, 3,110. Real property, £5,638. Pop., 610. Houses, 125. The living is a vicarage, annexed to Wombourne. There is a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
